---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="MCP Tools" description="Portal gateway to Valter's canonical MCP docs.">
  <h1>MCP Tools</h1>
  <span class="badge badge-dev">dev</span>

  <p>
    This page points to Valter's canonical MCP documentation. Valter currently
    exposes 31 MCP tools covering search, verification, reasoning, chat, judge
    profiling, and legal workflows. The MCP surface is available locally and
    remotely via HTTP/SSE, and has been submitted to the ChatGPT App Directory.
  </p>

  <p>
    In Valter's docs you will find the current connection settings, tool
    annotations with human-readable descriptions, and integration examples
    for Claude Desktop, ChatGPT, and other MCP-compatible agents.
  </p>

  <h2>What you will find in the canonical docs</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>Connection setup for local and remote MCP clients (HTTP/SSE with OAuth 2.0)</li>
    <li>31 tools with annotated descriptions and input schemas</li>
    <li>Prompting and agent integration examples</li>
    <li>Cross-links to Valter's REST API and architecture docs</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Canonical documentation</h2>

  <p>
    <a href="https://valter.sens.legal/api/mcp-tools/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
      Open Valter's full MCP documentation &rarr;
    </a>
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
